-- data-pipeline.fl — AI-powered data pipeline using stdlib + collection ops
-- Demonstrates: Filter, Sort, Group, Reduce, Map, Match, stdlib, Ask
-- Run: fluent run examples/data-pipeline.fl
-- Requires: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (falls back to mock without it)

Output "═══════════════════════════════════════════════".
Output "  AI-Powered Data Pipeline".
Output "═══════════════════════════════════════════════".
Output "".

-- ── Sample dataset ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Let transactions be a list containing
    a record with id "T001" amount 2500 category "SaaS" region "APAC" month "Jan",
    a record with id "T002" amount 890 category "Hardware" region "EMEA" month "Jan",
    a record with id "T003" amount 4200 category "SaaS" region "AMER" month "Feb",
    a record with id "T004" amount 310 category "Services" region "APAC" month "Feb",
    a record with id "T005" amount 7800 category "SaaS" region "AMER" month "Mar",
    a record with id "T006" amount 1200 category "Hardware" region "EMEA" month "Mar",
    a record with id "T007" amount 950 category "Services" region "AMER" month "Jan",
    a record with id "T008" amount 3300 category "SaaS" region "APAC" month "Mar".

-- ── Step 1: Stats ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Output "── Step 1: Dataset Summary ──".

Reduce transactions to count and call the result tx_count.
Output tx_count.

-- ── Step 2: Filter high-value ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 2: High-Value Transactions (>$2000) ──".

Filter transactions where amount is greater than 2000 and call the result high_value.
Reduce high_value to count and call the result hv_count.
Output hv_count.

-- ── Step 3: Sort by amount ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 3: Top Transactions by Amount ──".

Sort high_value by amount descending and call the result top_transactions.
Map top_transactions to id and call the result top_ids.
Output top_ids.

-- ── Step 4: Group by category ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 4: Grouped by Category ──".

Group transactions by category and call the result by_category.
Output by_category.

-- ── Step 5: Group by region ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 5: Grouped by Region ──".

Group transactions by region and call the result by_region.
Output by_region.

-- ── Step 6: Classify each transaction ────────────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 6: Classifying Transactions ──".

For each tx in top_transactions:
    Match tx.category:
        When "SaaS":     Output "  📊 Software revenue".
        When "Hardware":  Output "  🔧 Hardware revenue".
        When "Services":  Output "  🛠 Services revenue".
        Otherwise:        Output "  📦 Other revenue".
    End match.
End loop.

-- ── Step 7: AI summary (mock without API key) ─────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 7: AI Executive Summary ──".

@model(temperature: 0.3, max_tokens: 250)
Ask claude to "Write a 3-sentence executive summary of these transactions. Highlight the highest-value category and region." using data top_transactions and call the result summary.

Output summary.

-- ── Step 8: Risk assessment per transaction ──────────────────────────────────
Output "".
Output "── Step 8: Risk Flags ──".

For each tx in transactions:
    If tx.amount is greater than 5000, then output "  🚨 High-value flag:".
    Unless tx.amount is greater than 5000:
        Output "  ✓ Normal range".
    End unless.
End loop.

Output "".
Output "═══════════════════════════════════════════════".
Output "  Pipeline complete.".
Output "═══════════════════════════════════════════════".
